About

  A command line utility that reloads the active tab in chrome(*) when it is
  invoked.

  (*) Safari extension forthcoming, patches for other browsers welcome


Usage

  Open chrome, run the `reload-browser` executable, the current tab reloads
  
  Pairs well with `wach` (https://github.com/quackingduck/wach) e.g.:
  
    wach "make index.html && reload-browser"


Installation

  Install the command with npm:
    
    npm install -g reload-browser

  Then install the browser extension:

    reload-browser --install-chrome-extension
